# Responsive Layout Rules

Design mobile-first.

Use Tailwind breakpoints:
- Base: mobile
- `sm:` small screens
- `md:` tablets
- `lg:` laptops/desktops
- `xl:` large desktops
- `2xl:` very large screens

Prefer:
- `flex` for simple one-dimensional layouts
- `grid` for two-dimensional layouts
- `max-w-*` for readable content width
- `mx-auto` for centered containers
- `gap-*` instead of margin hacks
- `min-h-screen` only when full viewport layout is intended
- Responsive typography and spacing

Avoid:
- Fixed pixel widths
- Horizontal scrolling by accident
- Absolute positioning for normal layout
- Desktop-first layouts patched for mobile later
- Text blocks that are too wide
- Cards that stretch awkwardly on large screens

Every page should look good at:
- Mobile width
- Tablet width
- Desktop width
